\end{align*}t​∝x​Wheretttis training time in hours, andxxxis the size of the training data set in gigabytes.It is known that a certain machine learning model takes151515hours to train using a data set of size100100100gigabytes.Find an equation fortttin terms ofxxx.[2]If a dataset of 250 gigabytes is used, determine the expected training time.[2]The larger the data set that is used for training, the more effective the machine learning model is deemed to be.A new and improved training model has been developed, so that a machine learning model can be trained in the same amount of time as the previous model, using larger data sets. The equation for the new model ist=0.1xt=0.1xt=0.1x.Given a training time of202020hours, determine the difference in the size of the data sets between the first and second machine learning models.[3]

